#import "../book.typ": *
#startprayer("Psalm 92 · Mizmor Shir l’Yom haShabbat", "מִזְמוֹר שִׁיר לְיוֹם הַשַּׁבָּת")
#stanza("Mizmór shir l’yom haShabbat.",
  "מִזְמוֹר שִׁיר לְיוֹם הַשַּׁבָּת.", label:"Sung")
#stanza("Tov l’hodót la’Adonai, ul’zamér l’shimchá elyón. L’hagíd babóker chasdécha, ve’emunatchá baleilót. Alei-asór va’alei-nável, alei higayón b’chinór.",
  "טוֹב לְהֹדוֹת לַיְיָ וּלְזַמֵּר לְשִׁמְךָ עֶלְיוֹן. לְהַגִּיד בַּבֹּקֶר חַסְדֶּךָ וֶאֱמוּנָתְךָ בַּלֵּילוֹת. עֲלֵי־עָשׂוֹר וַעֲלֵי־נָבֶל עֲלֵי הִגָּיוֹן בְּכִנּוֹר.")
#stanza("Ki simachtáni Adonai b’fo’olécha, b’ma’aséi yadécha aranén. Mah gadlú ma’asécha Adonai, m’ód amkú machsh’votécha.",
  "כִּי שִׂמַּחְתַּנִי יְיָ בְּפׇעֳלֶךָ בְּמַעֲשֵׂי יָדֶיךָ אֲרַנֵּן. מַה־גָּדְלוּ מַעֲשֶׂיךָ יְיָ מְאֹד עָמְקוּ מַחְשְׁבֹתֶיךָ.")
#stanza("Ish-bá’ar lo yedá, uch’síl lo-yavín et-zot. Bifróach r’sha’ím k’mo-ésev, vayatzítzu kol-po’aléi áven, l’hishamdám adei-ád. V’atá maróm l’olám Adonai. Ki hiné oyvécha Adonai, ki-hiné oyvécha yovédu, yitpardú kol-po’aléi áven. Vatárem kir’ém karní, balotí b’shémen ra’anán. Vatabét einí b’shurái, bakamím alái m’re’ím tishmá’na oznái.",
  "אִישׁ־בַּעַר לֹא יֵדָע וּכְסִיל לֹא־יָבִין אֶת־זֹאת. בִּפְרֹחַ רְשָׁעִים כְּמוֹ־עֵשֶׂב וַיָּצִיצוּ כׇּל־פֹּעֲלֵי אָוֶן לְהִשָּׁמְדָם עֲדֵי־עַד. וְאַתָּה מָרוֹם לְעֹלָם יְיָ. כִּי הִנֵּה אֹיְבֶיךָ יְיָ כִּי־הִנֵּה אֹיְבֶיךָ יֹאבֵדוּ יִתְפָּרְדוּ כׇּל־פֹּעֲלֵי אָוֶן. וַתָּרֶם כִּרְאֵים קַרְנִי בַּלֹּתִי בְּשֶׁמֶן רַעֲנָן. וַתַּבֵּט עֵינִי בְּשׁוּרָי בַּקָּמִים עָלַי מְרֵעִים תִּשְׁמַעְנָה אׇזְנָי.", label:"Recited")
#stanza("Tzadík katamár yifrách, k’érez balvanón yisgé. Sh’tulím b’veit Adonai, b’chatzrót Elohéinu yafríchu.",
  "צַדִּיק כַּתָּמָר יִפְרָח כְּאֶרֶז בַּלְּבָנוֹן יִשְׂגֶּה. שְׁתוּלִים בְּבֵית יְיָ בְּחַצְרוֹת אֱלֹהֵינוּ יַפְרִיחוּ.", label:"Sung")
#stanza("Od y’nuvún b’seivá, d’shením v’ra’ananím yihyú. L’hagíd ki-yashár Adonai, tzurí v’lo-avláta bo.",
  "עוֹד יְנוּבוּן בְּשֵׂיבָה דְּשֵׁנִים וְרַעֲנַנִּים יִהְיוּ. לְהַגִּיד כִּי־יָשָׁר יְיָ צוּרִי וְלֹא־עַוְלָתָה בּוֹ.")
#eng("A psalm, a song for the day of Shabbat. It is good to give thanks to You, to sing to Your name, Most High — to tell of Your love in the morning and Your faithfulness through the nights, on the ten-stringed harp and the lyre, to the murmuring of the harp.")
#eng("You have gladdened me by what You have made; at the work of Your hands I sing for joy. How great are Your works — how deep beyond us are Your thoughts.")
#eng("A brutish person cannot know this, a fool cannot grasp it: though the wicked spring up like grass and all who do harm blossom, it is only to be destroyed forever — while You are exalted for all time. For look: those who set themselves against You, the ones who do harm, scatter and are undone.")
#eng("You have lifted my strength high; I am anointed with fresh oil. My eyes look out with confidence; my ears take in the fate of those who would rise against me.")
#engn("The just flourish like the date palm and grow tall like a cedar of Lebanon — planted in Your house, they blossom in the courtyards of our God. Even in old age they still bear fruit, staying full of sap and green — to declare that You are upright, my Rock, in whom there is no wrong.",
  [This is the only psalm in the whole book titled "for the Sabbath day," and it was the very song
  the Levites sang in the Temple each Shabbat. The Sages noticed it never once names Shabbat, and
  taught that it points past the week itself toward "the day that is entirely Shabbat" — the world
  we rehearse each Friday night.])

// ===================== PSALM 93 =====================
#startprayer("Psalm 93 · Adonai Malach", "יְיָ מָלָךְ")
#stanza("Adonai malách geút lavésh, lavésh Adonai oz hit’azár, af-tikón tevél bal-timót.",
  "יְיָ מָלָךְ גֵּאוּת לָבֵשׁ לָבֵשׁ יְיָ עֹז הִתְאַזָּר אַף־תִּכּוֹן תֵּבֵל בַּל־תִּמּוֹט.")
#stanza("Nachón kis’achá me’áz, me’olám áta. Nasú n’harót Adonai, nasú n’harót kolám, yisú n’harót dochyám.",
  "נָכוֹן כִּסְאֲךָ מֵאָז מֵעוֹלָם אָתָּה. נָשְׂאוּ נְהָרוֹת יְיָ נָשְׂאוּ נְהָרוֹת קוֹלָם יִשְׂאוּ נְהָרוֹת דׇּכְיָם.")
#stanza("Mikolót máyim rabím, adirím mishb’rei-yám, adír bamaróm Adonai.",
  "מִקֹּלוֹת מַיִם רַבִּים אַדִּירִים מִשְׁבְּרֵי־יָם אַדִּיר בַּמָּרוֹם יְיָ.")
#stanza("Edotécha ne’emnú m’ód, l’veitchá naavá-kódesh, Adonai l’órech yamím.",
  "עֵדֹתֶיךָ נֶאֶמְנוּ מְאֹד לְבֵיתְךָ נַאֲוָה־קֹדֶשׁ יְיָ לְאֹרֶךְ יָמִים.")
#eng("You reign, robed in majesty; robed and girded in strength. The world stands firm; it will not be shaken.")
#eng("Your throne stands firm from of old; from all eternity, You are. The rivers lift up — the rivers lift up their voice; the rivers lift up their roaring.")
#engn("Mightier than the thunder of great waters, mightier than the breakers of the sea, You are mighty on high. Your teachings are utterly trustworthy; holiness graces Your house for all the length of days.",
  [Short and surging, this psalm answers the flood: the waters lift their voice, yet mightier than
  the thunder of great waters is the Holy One on high. It is also the psalm of the sixth day, Friday —
  so as we complete the week we sing the same crowning the world sang when it was first complete.])
